<item>
            <title>[FLUME-2208] Jetty&apos;s default SocketSelector leaks File descriptors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-2208</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This causes each HTTP monitoring poll to leak one FD and each connection from an external client to HTTP Source to leak an FD when closed.  Each metrics poll causes lsof to show an FD that looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java 3317 root 173u sock 0,5 31374 can&apos;t identify protocol&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because of a half-closed socket, whose close is incomplete. &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/JETTY-597&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JETTY-597&lt;/a&gt; might be relevant.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
